- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the misalignment between technical and business stakeholders and proposes a business-driven approach to prioritize technical debt items, which can have implications for computational finance and science. 
- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is less likely as the paper does not deal with sound or music computing. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also less likely as the paper does not focus on programming languages specifically, but rather on the prioritization of technical debt items. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the least likely category as the paper does not deal with cryptography or security.
